  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>A bad DNS route could be cached to your Internet Service Provider (ISP) and may cause connectivity issues between your payment device and RepairQ. To resolve this issue, try using Google's DNS servers in your network settings.</p><h3 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:ChangeYourDNSServers-macOS-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934229721/Integrated+Payments+Troubleshooting+Resources\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934229721\" data-linked-resource-version=\"19\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payments: Troubleshooting Resources</a> </p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934786834/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+Windows+10\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934786834\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Devices: Changing Your DNS Servers - macOS Ventura</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295273/PAX+Device+Troubleshooting+Change+Your+DNS+Servers+-+macOS+Ventura\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295273\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Devices: Changing Your DNS Servers - Windows 10</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157/Integrated+Payment+Processing+-+Start+Here\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295157\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Processing - Start Here!</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185424.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h2 id=\"PAXDeviceTroubleshooting:ChangeYourDNSServers-macOS-UpdatingYourConnectionSettingsinmacOS\">Updating Your Connection Settings in macOS</h2><p /><p>1. On the upper-left of your desktop screen, click the <strong>Apple logo</strong>. From the dropdown, click <strong>System Preferences</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185430.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>2. On the System Preferences page, click <strong>Network</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185436.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>3. On the Network page, click <strong>Advanced</strong> on the lower-right side of the window.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185442.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>4. On the Advanced Network Settings page, click the <strong>DNS tab</strong> on the top row of available settings.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185450.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>5. Under the DNS Servers field, click the <strong>Add (+) button </strong>to add a server address. Type in the following two addresses:</p><ul><li><p>8.8.8.8</p></li><li><p>8.8.4.4</p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185608.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>6. After you have added the addresses, click <strong>OK </strong>to save your changes.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1934197007/image-20230608-185616.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>7. Close the settings windows and any active internet browsing sessions, then restart your connection to ensure that your changes go into effect.</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.18.X</p>",
